I too spent a long time planning what gear to go for, and passed up much better items, in order to get a selection of &quot;average&quot; items that also had a focus effect I wanted. <br>
<br>
It is completely ridiculous if casters will have to start over with five empty equipment slots on the first day of PoP.<br>
<br>
The least bloody solution is to scale existing level 3 focus items to work for spells up to level 65, and add a new set of PoP-only focus items that are more effective than the existing set, that also scale up to 65.<br>
<br>
Did I waste the last six months in EQ where the loot I went for was a Mask of Fall, Harla Dar's Talisman, Ring of Lightning, Hand of the Master - not to mention passing on a NTOV shoulder item, on the Strength of Elements, and on the 8th shawl because the slot was occupied by the ODS - whereas I could have gone for items with far better stats? <p><CENTER>
