<br>
Will melee haste items they worked hard to get STOP working at level 61?<br>
<br>
Will melee weapons stop procing at level 61?<br>
<br>
Will melee lose ANY effect on gear the moment they ding 61?<br>
<br>
Why should casters?<br>
<br>
The argument, they still work but not on your newest spells argument is also flawed.<br>
<br>
However if that is the case, than have all haste items STOP working on any newly acquired PoP weapons.<br>
<br>
Let it work on the older items, but require new haste for PoP weapons.<br>
<br>
Not to pick on melee, but there are only 2 classes when you think about it.<br>
<br>
Melee and Spell casters.<br>
<br>
The hybreds relie more on melee skills than casting.<br>
<br>
So this change hurts casters and not melee.<br>
<br>
Whoever thought up this change, needs to rethink it, unless focus items are readily available.<br>
<br>
Why cast any new spell, when you can cast your old one, with a mana reducing earring, a haste ring, and damage increaser bracer, if it yields the same results only faster and for less mana?<br>
<br>
Why are casters punished for leveling up, when melee haste items rewards are not decreased at all?<br>
